---
title: Sweet Chili Turkey Bowls with Bell Pepper & Candied Peanuts
description: Forget takeout: The path to sweet-and-savory dinner bliss is only 30 minutes away! In this recipe, pork, pepper, and onion are coated in a sumptuous sweet chili sauce, and peanuts are transformed into the perfect crunchy topping, along with citrusy cilantro. Everything comes together over a bed of fluffy lime-scented rice. The result? A symphony of flavors and textures so delicious, you might just lick the bowl.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6447d11c84d017c9de0d9f2c-03092082.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/649c8a854387a88e63f51404.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sweet-chili-turkey-bowls-649c8a854387a88e63f51404
author: Michelle Doll Olson
servings: 2
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: Asian
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 880 kcal
  fat: 34 g
  saturated fat: 12 g
  carbohydrates: 107 g
  sugar: 26 g
  protein: 36 g
  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 940 mg
---

Wash and dry produce.

Halve, core, and thinly slice @red bell pepper{1} into strips. Halve, peel, and
thinly slice @yellow onion{1}(halved, peeled, and thinly sliced). Zest and
quarter @lime{1}(zested and quartered). Finely chop @cilantro{¼%ounce}(finely
chopped).

In a small #pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{¾%cup}, 1¼ cups water, and a pinch
of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook
until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, heat a large, preferably #nonstick pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add @peanuts{½%ounce}, 2 TBSP water, and @sugar{1%tsp}. Cook, stirring
often, until water has evaporated and peanuts are coated and lightly toasted,
~{3-5%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a small #bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in same pan over medium-high
heat. Add bell pepper and onion; season with @salt and @pepper. Cook, stirring,
until tender and lightly browned, ~{6-9%minutes}.

Transfer veggies to a #plate{}.

Add a drizzle of @cooking oil{} to same pan over medium-high heat. Add
@ground turkey{10%ounce}; season with @salt and @pepper. Using a #spatula{},
press into an even layer. Cook, undisturbed, until browned on bottom,
~{3-4%minutes}.

Break up meat into pieces and continue cooking until pork is cooked through,
~{2-4%minutes}.

Stir in veggies, then add @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon}, @sweet Thai chili
sauce{1%ounce}, and @butter{1%tablespoon}. Cook, stirring, until mixture is
thoroughly coated, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} and lime zest to taste.
Season with @salt.

Divide rice between bowls and top with pork mixture, peanuts, and cilantro.
Serve with lime wedges on the side.

> Swap in beef or turkey for pork.

> Ground Turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.